				 Minister quits over clashes

 OUR CORRESPONDENT
																								Brahmanigaon (Kondhmal), Dec. 28: An Orissa minister today resigned over the past three days communal violence in Kondhmal while chief minister Naveen Patnaik ordered a judicial probe and changed the district collector.
																								State steel and mines minister Padmanabha Behera, who is from Kondhmal, quit the cabinet owning moral responsibility for the flare-up in several villages during which churches and houses were torched and at least two persons killed.
																								Central forces today carried out a flag march in Daringibadi, Baliguda and Barakhamba. The district police want marches also in the surrounding areas, where an armed mob attacked a village yesterday, prompting police firing that killed one person.
																								Retired high court judge Basudev Panigrahi will conduct the inquiry into the circumstances that led to the clashes. Malkangiri collector Manish Verma has been appointed Kondhmal collector replacing B. Mohapatra. 

